<item>
            <title>[LU-15929] Correct the net selection for router ping</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15929</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;lnet_select_best_ni_on_local_net() contains logic for restricting&lt;br/&gt;
the NI selection to a net specified by lnet_peer::lp_disc_net_id. The&lt;br/&gt;
purpose of this is to ensure that LNet peers ping every interface on&lt;br/&gt;
a router at a regular interval as part of the LNet router health&lt;br/&gt;
feature. However, this logic is flawed in because lnet_msg_discovery()&lt;br/&gt;
is used to determine whether the message being sent is a discovery&lt;br/&gt;
message, but that function actually determines whether a give message&lt;br/&gt;
can &lt;em&gt;trigger&lt;/em&gt; discovery&lt;/p&gt;</description>
